Do you need `Wants` ?
same as below.
wants is enough for poweron? will confirm
I am not familiar with state mgmt, I would like to review by some experts on this.
Ack

is there any dependency with phosphor-debug-collector ? I mean do we need to make sure any service files which are present in phosphor-debug-collector dependent with this service file ? If so, do you need `After` or `Before`?
yes there is a dependency.. so will add an after

start_host@.service (i.e. sbe start) is run within obmc-host-starting@0.target so if we need to ensure this service runs after it, you'll need an explicit After= clause:
After=start_host@0.service

One confusing thing though is that Jayanth stated we need this to run after start SBE but before hostboot starts. We have no control over that. Once you start the SBE, hostboot will automatically be started within 30 seconds. I'm sure this service will be up and running before that though so probably not an issue.
Done
This should be removed, it's redundant since it will always run after "obmc-host-starting"
Done
These (lines 6 and 7) are also redundant since for the host to be started, the power has to be on.
Done

I would also add this to ensure mapper has introspected your service before officially being started:
Before=mapper-wait@-org-open_power-dump-manager.service
Done
This isn't needed anymore since we have the full path in ExecStart now
Done
Missed this, not sure why the "" are required around the service here and the next line?
Done

Do you need to make sure SBE is ready to accept chipops?
start_host just trigger istep0 and it will wait for SBE to boot and come out if booted.
adding check for SBE state once it is ready

I'm not familiar with the use of {BUSNAME} here. I can't find any documentation on it. I assume it uses the service name (i.e. org.open_power.Dump.Manager?). Why not just code the specific service like all the other services?
